author: Mia McCurdy
reviewBody: When you're leaving the cathedral you might as well keep exploring that end and head on over to NUIG. The campus is gorgeous. I love wandering around university grounds and this place is great. You'll feel like you're in Harry Potter for a bit!
name: University of Galway

author: frank egbuna
reviewBody: It is calm now because of COVID but the library is open. The library is a great place to read however you have to reserve a seat online.
name: University of Galway

author: Aparajita Chaturvedi
reviewBody: Nice place to study. Has high academic standard's and helping faculty staff..
name: University of Galway

author: Jordan Sg
reviewBody: Under such a pandemic situation its completely unnecessary to increase the course fee . Rather the university could have tried to lower it to help the students . At least increase the scholarships . Pls consider as there are lots of aspirants who wish to study in NUI.
name: University of Galway

author: Dat Nguyen
reviewBody: Great university with beautiful campus
name: University of Galway

author: Chris “quackman” V
reviewBody: huge, old campus a pleasure to walk around. Very nice dorms which are also rentable rooms when main semesters are over. big cafeteria. Nice overall area with plenty to do outside the Uni.
name: University of Galway

author: Matthias Cowley
reviewBody: First it was Queen's College, then University College - and now it's National University of Ireland, Galway. But to thousands of graduates, it was always their most cherished alma mater!
name: University of Galway

author: Libin Philip
reviewBody: Beautiful and Lively campus...I enjoy every moment studying here!
name: University of Galway

author: Google User
reviewBody: Top 1% Worldwide. Nice atmosphere
name: University of Galway

author: angie jinx
reviewBody: Great university. Still studying and enjoying the experience. I would definitely recommend any adults thinking of going back to education to give this uni a good looking at as it is one of th e best.
name: University of Galway

author: Violet Ewohime-Ndukaire
reviewBody: It's was a great Graduation ceremony today.
name: University of Galway

author: Matthew Ajimati
reviewBody: Excellent citadel of learning. Collegial and multicultural environment for students and academics.

author: Stephy
reviewBody: Nice to walk around the campuses
name: University of Galway

author: Min Zhang
reviewBody: Beautiful campus, especially in the autumn
name: University of Galway

author: Ahmed Kabir
reviewBody: Lovely and large campus. Beautiful infrastructure and architecture. Well Known and one of the best universities in Ireland. Plenty of asian students studying here with scholarships. Different scholarship schemes for foreign students. Located at the heart of the city. Vibrant atomosphere.
name: University of Galway

author: Shane Cunningham
reviewBody: Great campus locate beside the River Corrib. Lots of place to eat and easy to get around on foot or by bicycle. They have spent a lot of time and effort renovating the campus over the last 15 years
name: University of Galway

author: Sagar Arora
reviewBody: If not as a student, you have to check out the luring architecture of this place as a traveller!
name: University of Galway

author: Soumitra Sinha
reviewBody: Ranked in top 1% amongst the universities across the globe, this university has one of the greenest buildings in whole Ireland, with so many international students and such a great campus all along the River Corrib, makes this university a great place to enhance your life.
name: University of Galway

author: Aoife O' Leary
reviewBody: Went to a play dealing with being bullied shocking and disturbing dealing with issues of hate relatable to anyone who went through a difficult childhood of not being accepted by others
name: University of Galway

author: Kweeveen Campbell
reviewBody: Great campus, excellent learning done here, good social scene, very safe and secure, helpful staff both academic and support
name: University of Galway
